    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p class="land-overview-text">
      Sustainable land use planning is essential for balancing human needs with environmental protection. 
      UHWF works closely with local communities, village councils, district authorities and other stakeholders 
      to develop participatory, equitable and climate-resilient land use plans that secure land rights, 
      reduce conflicts and protect critical wildlife corridors and grazing areas.
    </p>

    <h2>Key Activities</h2>
    <ul class="land-check-list">
      <li>Participatory village land use planning (VLUP)</li>
      <li>Mapping wildlife corridors and grazing areas</li>
      <li>Supporting sustainable agriculture and settlement planning</li>
      <li>Land conflict resolution mechanisms</li>
      <li>Climate-resilient land management practices</li>
    </ul>

